-- MOVES-Gottex taps ex-HSBC exec to develop multi asset unit
-- By Nishant Kumar
-- Tue Sep 09, 2014 10:29AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 9 (Reuters) - Gottex Fund Management <GFMN.S> has hired former HSBC <HSBA.L> executive James Hughes to help develop institutional business for its multi asset investment unit.

Hughes will join the Swiss money manager in October and report to Michael Azlen, the firm said in a statement on Tuesday.